modules.description: This module implements a basic graph pattern (BGP) query engine over PostgreSQL-stored RDF data. It provides term conversion, comparison, and lookup operations for RDF terms, along with subject and object enumeration. Core functionality includes translating RDF terms to and from an internal representation and executing SPARQL-like triple pattern queries against a PostgreSQL-backed RDF graph.

This module provides PostgreSQL-backed management of RDF graphs with triple-level CRUD operations, transaction control, and namespace mapping. It supports graph handles and triple data structures for persistent RDF storage with transactional guarantees, enabling applications like semantic web systems and data integration platforms. The included query engine translates RDF terms and executes SPARQL-like triple pattern queries, offering term conversion, comparison, and enumeration capabilities. Advanced features such as graph state duplication, blank node ID generation, and metadata access enhance complex data synchronization and querying workflows.

This module implements a PostgreSQL-backed RDF storage system with full triple-level CRUD operations, transaction control, and namespace management. It provides data structures for graph handles and triples, supporting SPARQL-like querying through pattern matching and term translation. Users can perform operations such as inserting and querying RDF triples, managing graph states, and handling blank node identifiers. Example use cases include semantic web applications and data integration pipelines requiring persistent, transactional RDF storage.

This module offers a PostgreSQL-based RDF storage system with comprehensive support for triple-level CRUD operations, transaction management, and namespace handling. It includes data structures for graphs and RDF triples, enabling SPARQL-like queries via pattern matching and term translation. Users can insert and query triples, manage graph states, and work with blank nodes. Example applications include semantic web services and data integration systems requiring persistent, transactional RDF storage.
